article.linkText: Asamoah's 22 lead East Tennessee State over Alabama A&M 82-71
article.story: CLEVELAND -- — Ebby Asamoah scored 22 points as East Tennessee State beat Alabama A&M 82-71 on Friday night. Quimari Peterson scored 21 points, shooting 7 for 12 (4 for 6 from 3-point range) and 3 of 4 from the free-throw line for the Buccaneers (3-3). Jaden Seymour finished with 13 points. Dailin Smith led the way for the Bulldogs (0-4) with 20 points and six rebounds. Alabama A&M also got 15 points from Omari Peek-Green. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
